      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Gate repair lane and tune concurrency",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a default-off repair-lane feature flag: `CLAWSWEEPER_FEATURE_REPAIR_ENABLED=1` is now required before ClawSweeper dispatches live repair workers or performs repair mutations.\n- Keep the safe/read-only parts available when the flag is unset: review routing, planning, scanning, dry-run requeue/self-heal summaries, and reports still run without starting executing repair workers.\n- Move repair/automerge/issue-implementation throughput to explicit automation limits, capped at one live run by default.\n- Prefer existing portable `gitcrawl-store` SQLite state before the legacy local gitcrawl DB, so sweeps can reuse refreshed issue/PR context instead of depending on an ad hoc local crawl.\n- Document migrated repair features, rollout expectations, gitcrawl-store freshness, and add regression coverage for limits, workflow env wiring, unset/set repair dispatch routing, and gitcrawl-store defaults.\n\n## What This Means Operationally\nClawSweeper keeps doing its normal review/triage/reporting work by default. The new repair lane is an optional add-on: it can notice repair opportunities and write/read planning output, but it will not create live repair worker runs, invoke Codex to mutate branches, open repair PRs, or continue automerge/issue-implementation repair loops unless `CLAWSWEEPER_FEATURE_REPAIR_ENABLED=1` is set for that repository.\n\nWhen enabled, dispatch is intentionally slow and bounded: the default repair capacity is one live repair run at a time, one live automerge repair run, one live issue-implementation run, and one issue-implementation dispatch per sweep. Existing execute/fix/merge gates still apply; this flag only opens the repair feature lane, it does not bypass the older mutation protections.\n\n## Rollout Note\nThis is intentionally default-off because ClawSweeper runs across many repositories. Repositories that should keep live repair/autofix/automerge/issue-implementation dispatch must explicitly set `CLAWSWEEPER_FEATURE_REPAIR_ENABLED=1`. Repositories that do not set it keep read-only review, scan, plan, and report behavior without starting executing repair workers.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm run check`\n",
